trend_summary: Across the sequence the area remains dominantly agricultural–forest terrain. Built forms stay scattered and limited to small villages; only minor edge-growth and a few new farm complexes appear. Some woodland on the western hills is cleared then partly regenerated, while eastern fields become more regular. Overall change is modest with no major urbanisation.
notable_changes: Minor outward expansion of village footprints in the north-east sector.
Construction of several new farm buildings/greenhouses near the central lowlands.
Selective forest clearance on western ridges followed by patches of regrowth.
Upgrading and slight realignment of the main east–west road corridor.
